The paper deals with visual dialog, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a general attention mechanism, which falls under the scope of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also uses factor graphs, which are commonly used in probabilistic graphical models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which falls under the scope of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
